    "body": "I think if a web3 client is allowed to connect and query the RPC WHILE it is still syncing and catching up, it get into this bad state for some reason...\r\n\r\nBlocking off all inbound while syncing and only opening the firewall after its synced to head seem to make the node more stable. There's a bug somewhere on L2GETH while it is catching up to head.",
